    "headerDoc": "STEP 969 — Davenport Constant: Exhaustive Computational Proofs\n  藤本伸樹 2026-04-22\n\n  Davenport constant D(G) of a finite abelian group G:\n    D(G) = smallest d ∈ ℕ s.t. every length-d sequence over G has\n           a non-empty subsequence summing to 0 (identity).\n    Equivalently: D(G) - 1 = longest sequence with NO non-empty zero-sum subseq.\n\n  This complements Paper 127's EGZ work via the relation (cyclic case):\n    E(ℤ_n) = D(ℤ_n) + n - 1  (Gao 1996)\n  With D(ℤ_n) = n we recover E(ℤ_n) = 2n - 1 (EGZ 1961).\n\n  Known small values:\n    D(ℤ_n) = n for all n ≥ 1 (Davenport 1966, elementary).\n    "
  },
